"Vietnamese People's Newspaper Online - Vietnamese Prime Minister Phan Minh Chinh attends the third National Digital Technology Enterprise Development Forum in Vietnam."
"During the third National Digital Technology Enterprise Development Forum in Vietnam, two major conferences were held, discussing topics centered around the relationship between digital technology enterprises and the nation's digital transformation, and the economic recovery and development of digital technology enterprises during and after the COVID-19 pandemic, with a focus on two main themes."
"Minister of Information and Communications Ruan Meng Xiong stated that in 2021, despite the ongoing spread of COVID-19, the number and revenue of digital technology enterprises in Vietnam still showed growth momentum, reaching close to 10%."
"In 2021, the number of typical digital products in Vietnam was cultivated, focusing on addressing major challenges faced by Vietnam. Many digital products have gone abroad and the ranking of Vietnam's digital technology has improved."
"Minister Ruan Meng Xiong called on digital technology enterprises to shoulder the responsibility of developing the platform for the nation's digital transformation, stating that taking on the task of developing these digital platforms is a national mission."
"At the forum, leaders from various departments and government agencies, as well as businesses, organizations, and individuals who are studying, developing, applying, and transferring digital technology, shared their mobilization and gathering of resources from society as a whole to develop Vietnam's technology enterprises, and worked together to promote the nation's digital transformation, as well as breakthrough ideas and solutions for post-pandemic economic recovery."
"Prime Minister Fan Ming Zheng emphasized in his speech at the forum that digital transformation is the way of the world and an objective requirement for development."
"Digital transformation has become a global issue and serves the entire population, therefore, it requires the mobilization of the entire population to participate."
The people and businesses are the core, main body, goal, and driving force of the digital transformation.
Therefore, all policies must be for the people and enterprises.
Prime Minister Fan Mingzheng emphasized that digital transformation must reflect the national spirit and should be driven primarily by internal strength, with strategy, a long-term, and decisive factor, while external strength should be an important and breakthrough point.
The Prime Minister emphasized that digital transformation needs to reflect the national spirit and should be driven by internal factors as the main, strategic, long-term, and decisive factors, with external factors as important breakthroughs. He also believes that digital transformation needs to drive the development towards depth and sustainability, to participate in COVID-19 pandemic prevention and control, economic recovery and development, to respond to subsequent changes, overcome the phenomenon of natural resource depletion, and support green transformation and green energy development.
The digital transformation needs to participate in the establishment of databases to protect and promote cultural values, historical traditions, and local customs of the country. It should drive the digital transformation in fields such as banking, taxation, land management and development databases as well as logistics.
The ultimate goal of digital transformation is to make people happier and to promote the prosperity and development of the country.
Premier Fan Mingzheng emphasized the need for governments at all levels, institutions, and businesses to increase their leadership and guidance in the development of digital technology, to enhance their understanding of digital transformation, to continue to develop and improve the system for digital transformation, and to strengthen national management while promoting the development of digital technology companies with a spirit of respect, communication, listening, positivity, and initiative.
During the forum, Prime Minister Fan Mingzheng attended the 2021 "Vietnam Manufacturing" Award Ceremony for Outstanding Digital Products and the opening ceremony of the "Vietnam Manufacturing" Digital Product Exhibition.